Executive Profile
Richard S. Stoddart  Chairman of Leo Burnett North America and Chief Executive Officer of Leo Burnet Worldwide, Publicis Groupe S.A.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships54--
Background

		Mr. Richard Stoddart, also known as Rich, has been Global President of Network at Leo Burnett Company, Inc. since January 2017. Mr. Stoddart served as the Global Chief Executive Officer of Leo Burnett Company, Inc. since February 1, 2016 until January 2017. Mr. Stoddart served as the Chief Executive Officer of Leo Burnet - North America at Publicis Groupe SA from 2015 to 2016. Mr. Stoddart has been the President of Arc Worldwide, Inc. since January 2007. He has been ... a Manager of Marketing Communications at Ford overseeing creative and media strategy and execution since 2001 and is responsible for managing Ford's Marketing Communications department and annual budget of upwards of $800 million and agency relationships. He served as the President of North America Operations at Leo Burnett Worldwide, Inc. since December 2004. He served as the Manager of Marketing Communications at Ford Motor Company. He served at both Ford Motor Company and sister Publicis Groupe agency Fallon, based in Minneapolis for 10 years. He was responsible for several high-profile initiatives including the “Ford on Ford“ brand campaign, the successful F-150 launch and the launch of six new vehicles as well as Ford's “Built For The Road Ahead“ campaign in 2005. Mr. Stoddart serves as Chairman of Leo Burnett North America at Publicis Groupe SA. Mr. Stoddart served as Director of Account Management for Fallon and a Member of its Minneapolis Management team and was responsible for all facets of the office including profitability, culture, account leadership and new business. From 1999 to 2001, he was responsible for the account management function at Fallon and served as the Senior Agency Representative on Ralston Purina Pet Foods, Lee Jeans, Macromedia and Long John Silvers. He led the new business pitch for Miller Lite -- one of Fallon's most significant and high profile wins. During his tenure at Fallon, he served as Group Director for Miller Lite and Ralston Purina, two of the agency's largest accounts, from 1997 to 1999 and Management Supervisor on Ralston from 1995 to 1997. Mr. Stoddart served at Leo Burnett for 10 years, as a Media Buyer/planner on Hewlett-Packard since 1985 and a transition to Account Management to begin working on clients such as Keebler, Tropicana and McDonald's. He served as Vice President and Account Supervisor since 1993. He served at McDonald's youth business as an Account Director since 1994. He has been an Independent Director at Hasbro Inc. since March 27, 2014. He serves as Director of Carbon Media Group LLC. Mr. Stoddart has led the push into branded entertainment at Ford with the development of several brand integration programs and partnerships including “American Idol,“ “24,“ “Extreme Makeover: Home Edition“ and “American Dreams.“ He serves as Vice Chair of American Advertising Federation, Inc and has been its Director since June 7, 2013. While at Ford, Mr. Stoddart was also a recipient of the prestigious American Advertising Federation “Hall of Fame“ Achievement Award in 2002, recognizing advertising professionals under the age of 40 who have demonstrated outstanding career achievements with measurable results. Mr. Stoddart completed his Bachelors in Arts in American Government at Dartmouth College in 1985.Read Full Background




